  "description": [
    "Art Plays Noble Role in War by Preserving Ideals Amid Ruthlessness A A__ Conflict Is Antagonistic to Spirit of Creative Work Also Affects Ranks World Is Still Suffering From Injuries Caused by Last European Outbreak By Leila Mechlin Art In wartime might seem too trivial compared with great issues at stake even to be given consideration were it not that memory and record persist of the part it nobly played a quarter of a century ago when the devastating flames of the socalled Great War swept Europe as they threaten to do today the spark having already been lit To those who lived at that time and as adults were deeply concerned therewith these memories are very vivid andfr f rw tlvrtro nHn mira rrrnnm im einoa convincing evidence is available in the publications of the day Obviously war is antagonistic to art being primarily destructive rather than constructive and suffers not only as a product of civilization which is outraged but because its creative source the artist suffers In undue proportion It is impossible to hurt the artist and not hurt art Prom the injuries done 25 years ago the art of this country as well as that of"
